Since $ABCD$ is a trapezoid, $\angle ABC = 180^{\circ} - 110^{\circ} = 70^{\circ}$ and $\angle BCD = 180^{\circ} - 100^{\circ} = 80^{\circ}$. Therefore, $\angle ABX = 180^{\circ} - 70^{\circ} = 110^{\circ}$ and $\angle CDY = 180^{\circ} - 80^{\circ} = 100^{\circ}$.

Now, $\angle BAX + \angle ABX + \angle BXA = 180^{\circ}$, so $\angle BXA = 180^{\circ} - 110^{\circ} - x = 70^{\circ} - x$. Similarly, $\angle DYX + \angle CDY + \angle DXY = 180^{\circ}$, so $\angle DXY = 180^{\circ} - 100^{\circ} - y = 80^{\circ} - y$.

Finally, $\angle AFD = \angle BXA + \angle DXY = (70^{\circ} - x) + (80^{\circ} - y) = 150^{\circ} - (x + y)$. But since $x + y = 110^{\circ}$, $\angle AFD = 150^{\circ} - 110^{\circ} = \boxed{40^{\circ}}$.

