The sum of the angles in a quadrilateral is $360^\circ$.  Therefore, we have $$\angle A + \angle B + \angle C + \angle D = 360^\circ.$$Substituting the given angle measures, we get $$110^\circ + 100^\circ + \angle C + 100^\circ = 360^\circ,$$which implies $\angle C = 50^\circ$.

