answer:
Recall that the measure of an inscribed angle is half the measure of the intercepted arc. Furthermore, the measure of the central angle is equal to the measure of its intercepted arc. Thus, the sum of the measures of the central angles of a circle is $360^\circ$. We can use this information to find the measure of $\alpha$. \begin{align*}
\alpha &= 360^\circ - \frac{1}{2}(105^\circ + 110^\circ) - \frac{1}{2}(180^\circ - 170^\circ) \\
&= 360^\circ - \frac{1}{2}(215^\circ) - \frac{1}{2}(10^\circ) \\
&= 360^\circ - 112.5^\circ - 5^\circ \\
&= \boxed{242.5^\circ}
\end{align*}

