The graph of the equation $x^2 - y^2 + 6x + 16y - 46 = 0$ is a hyperbola.  Completing the square in $x$ and $y$, we get $$(x^2 + 6x + 9) - (y^2 - 16y + 64) = -9 + 64 - 46,$$or $$(x + 3)^2 - (y - 8)^2 = -9.$$This hyperbola has center $(-3,8)$.

