The complex number $a + bi$ is at a distance of $\sqrt{a^2 + b^2}$ from the origin in the complex plane.  We want this distance to be at most 5, so $a^2 + b^2 \le 5^2 = 25$.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

fill((-5,-5)--(-5,5)--(5,5)--(5,-5)--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw((-5,-5)--(-5,5)--(5,5)--(5,-5)--cycle);
draw(Circle((0,0),5));
draw((-5,0)--(5,0));
draw((0,-5)--(0,5));

label("$-5$",(-5,0),S);
label("$5$",(5,0),S);
label("$-5$",(0,-5),W);
label("$5$",(0,5),E);
[/asy]

Thus, we want to find the number of lattice points that lie in or on the boundary of the disk centered at the origin with radius 5.  By inspection, there are $\boxed{81}$ such lattice points.

