There are 13 choices for the value of $a$, and for each value of $a$, there are at most 11 choices for $b$.  We must be careful, however, when $a = \pm 5$, because in this case, there are only 7 choices for $b$.  Thus, there are $13 \cdot 11 - 2 \cdot 4 = \boxed{141}$ such ordered pairs.

