O = (0,0);
Q = (1,0);
P = (1.2,0.5);
R = (0.8,0.1);
S = (-0.8,0.1);
T = (-0.8,-0.1);
U = (0.8,-0.1);
V = (0.2,0.7);
W = (0.5,-0.4);
X = (0.8,0.7);

draw(O--P,red);
draw(O--Q);
draw(Q--P,red);
draw(O--R);
draw(O--S);
draw(O--T);
draw(O--U);
draw(O--V);
draw(O--W);
draw(O--X);
draw(R--S--T--U--V--W--X--cycle);
draw(Q--R);
draw(Q--S);
draw(Q--T);
draw(Q--U);
draw(Q--V);
draw(Q--W);
draw(Q--X);

label("$O$", O, SW);
label("$P$", P, NE);
label("$Q$", Q, S);
label("$R$", R, NW);
label("$S$", S, SW);
label("$T$", T, SE);
label("$U$", U, NE);
label("$V$", V, S);
label("$W$", W, SE);
label("$X$", X, NE);
[/asy]

Thus, $PQ = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{s^2}{2}} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(\frac{PQ}{\cos \theta}\right)^2}$.  Substituting $PQ = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{s^2}{2}}$, we get $\sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{s^2}{2}} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(\frac{OP \sin \theta}{\cos \theta}\right)^2}$, so $OP^2 - \frac{s^2}{2} = OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot OP^2 \tan^2 \theta$.  Thus, $\tan^2 \theta = 2 - \frac{s^2}{OP^2}$.

Since $PQ = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{s^2}{2}}$, we have $PQ = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(\frac{OP \sin \theta}{\cos \theta}\right)^2} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot OP^2 \tan^2 \theta} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(2 - \frac{s^2}{OP^2}\right)OP^2} = \sqrt{OP^2 - OP^2 + \frac{s^2}{2}} = \sqrt{\frac{s^2}{2}} = \frac{s}{\sqrt{2}}$.

Thus, $PQ = \frac{s}{\sqrt{2}}$, so $PQ = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{s^2}{2}} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(\frac{OP \sin \theta}{\cos \theta}\right)^2} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot OP^2 \tan^2 \theta} = \sqrt{OP^2 - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left(2 - \frac{s^2}{OP^2}\right)OP^2} = \sqrt{OP^2 - OP^2 + \frac{s^2}{2}} = \sqrt{\frac{s^2}{2}} = \frac{s}{\sqrt{2}}$.

Thus, the distance from $P$ to the sixth vertex is $\boxed{10}$.

